GENERAL REQUIREMENTS APPLICABALE FOR EVERY VISA TYPE 
- A national passport,
valid for at least three months after the expiration date of the requested visa and having at least 2 blank visa designated pages, not to be issued more than 10 years ago. Copies of travel documents (PASSPORT) are not accepted;
- Application form
(application form have to be filled on-line (please apply online at
http://visa.mfa.gov.ua (http://visa.mfa.gov.ua/)
). After completing forms prompted to save the file in .pdf format. This file have to be printed and signed);
- 1 photo
- recent, passport-sized, resembling applicant's travel document photo;
- Payment of consular fee.
Money transfer receipt for visa fee and a copy of it (payment reference is applicants surname, separate payment should be done for each visa application);
- Proof of the applicant’s financial sufficiency
for the intended period of stay and return to the country of origin, or transit to a third country, or the possibility to legally obtain sufficient financial means on the territory of Ukraine, as required by the Rules for proving financial sufficiency of foreigners and stateless persons for entry to Ukraine, stay on the territory of Ukraine, transit through the territory of Ukraine and departure from Ukraine, and establishment of the amount of such sufficiency, approved by the Resolution of the Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine of 4 December 2013 no.884. When multi-entry visa is requested, financial sufficiency for the first planned visit to Ukraine shall be considered. Holders of diplomatic or service passport shall be exempt from this requirement;
- Valid international
travel or medical (health) insurance
. Valid health insurance with coverage of at least 30,000 EUR or equivalent in other currency, unless otherwise stipulated by legislation or international treaties of Ukraine. When multi-entry visa is requested, availability of health insurance valid for the first intended visit to Ukraine shall be considered. Holders of diplomatic or service passport shall be exempt from this requirement;
- Together with all items listed above the following documents, each hereinafter referred to as "the supporting document", related to the purpose of entry, must be submitted for visas (section “Visa types”).
If you submit a child's passport, it should be accompanied by a joint request of both parents with signatures certified by JP, Police, Notary Public and copy of the child’s certificate of birth.
Please note: The Consular office has full authority to evaluate and request more documents than those submitted by the applicant. The latter is hereby informed that submitting the aforementioned documents does not guarantee automatic issuance of the visa.
Documents specific to Transit Visas 
One of the following:
Visa for another country (if required) and tickets;
or
Document confirming that passengers/cargo are to transit through Ukraine by car/coach;
or
International carrier license issued by the relevant authority of a foreign state;
Please note that applicants might be asked for additional documents by Ukraine’s visa officers (e.g. return flight tickets and other documents confirming applicants’ circumstances (to be defined by Ukraine’s visa officers of the relevant Embassy/Consulate General).

